Program: Free Thinking
Title: Developments in Neuroscience, Krzysztof Zanussi, Peaceful Resistance
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b05pr72s
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 9 Apr 2015
Rana Mitter discusses a new model for understanding the brain, with researcher and writer Norman Doidge. Polish film director Krzysztof Zanussi talks about his latest film - Foreign Body - and a new touring festival of classic Polish cinema selected by Martin Scorsese. Activist Srdja Popovic is a proponent of non-violent protest and was a founder of the student movement Otpor! which helped to bring about the downfall of Slobodan Milosevic. He and writer Kate Maltby talk about the strengths and weaknesses of peaceful resistance. Producer: Torquil MacLeod. Show less